The locale registry (config/localization/locale_registry.yaml) has all four Chinese markets fully defined \'97 zh-CN, zh-TW, zh-HK, zh-SG \'97 with TTS providers, voice defaults, storefront IDs, and distribution rules. The brand locale extension file already has 6 zh-TW pilot brands defined (sleep_repair_tw, stabilizer_tw, etc.), and catalog_planner.py is already locale-aware \'97 it reads from that extension file and resolves locale from brand config automatically. So the planning layer requires no code changes.\
