google play spam detection\
Google Play employs automated models and human reviewers to detect spam across apps and content like books or audiobooks. This system flags violations such as repetitive uploads, low-quality AI-generated audio, or misleading metadata, which is highly relevant for audiobook producers aiming to avoid account suspensions.\
App Spam Policies\
Apps spamming users or the store through unsolicited messages, repetitive content, or unauthorized web views face removal. Google prohibits message spam without user confirmation of content and recipients, as well as apps duplicating existing experiences without unique value.\
\
Books and Audiobooks Policies\
Prohibited content includes unwanted promotions, free online duplicates, mass solicitations, or low-quality machine-read audio. Metadata mimicking existing titles or poor file quality triggers flags, with automated tools accelerating detection.\
Detection and Enforcement\
A mix of AI models scans for issues faster, backed by trained analysts for context. Violations lead to content removal, preview disabling, account suspension, or payment holds; appeals are possible via notifications. For publishers, public domain duplicates are rejected except from select partners.\
Avoidance Tips\
Ensure original, high-quality content with accurate metadata; avoid bulk similar uploads or promotional samples. Test AI-generated audiobooks for natural pacing to bypass low-quality flags, aligning with platform guidelines for self-publishers.\
